{
  "texts": [
    "An identical protocol to that above was used for point cloud generation and clustering.",
    "Evaluation criteriaSeveral evaluation strategies have been used for binding site prediction.",
    "The traditional metrics of area under the receiver operator characteristic curve (AUROC) or accuracy are not appropriate for imbalanced problems as very high scores can be achieved by predicting all residues as non-binding [62].",
    "DCA, DCC, DVO or atom IoU (Table 1) are commonly used, however DCC, DVO and IoU are based on the assumption that the ligand in the PDB complex is the perfect ligand.",
    "While this may be the case, it is not certain, and so we opted to use DCA to evaluate and compare our prediction method, where we measure success by whether the centre of the predicted site is within 4Å of any ligand heavy atom."
  ]
}